The paper focuses on using multiple robots for exploring and mapping environments, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of constellations for compressing descriptions of places visited by robots involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The method for extracting compact spatial and semantic descriptors of objects in a scene involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed method for decentralized loop closure verification involves both machine learning and control systems (cs.LG and cs.SY). Overall, the paper covers a range of topics that could fit into multiple sub-categories, but the focus on robotics and computer vision make cs.RO and cs.CV the most likely categories.
